WEBVTT

00:01.875 --> 00:03.542
OH, I HATE FINALS.

00:03.542 --> 00:06.083
WHAT KIND OF A SADIST BASES
1/3 OF A SEMESTER'S GRADE

00:06.083 --> 00:07.500
ON WHETHER OR NOT
YOU CAN RECITE THE OPENING

00:07.500 --> 00:09.458
TO THE CANTERBURY TALES
IN PERFECT MIDDLE ENGLISH?

00:09.458 --> 00:11.542
JOEY, WE'VE BEEN OVER
THIS A THOUSAND TIMES.

00:11.542 --> 00:13.834
YOUR PRONUNCIATION
IS FLAWLESS.

00:13.834 --> 00:14.959
MAYBE SO, BUT I'M STILL GONNA
CONTINUE TORTURING MYSELF

00:14.959 --> 00:17.542
UNTIL TEST TIME.
I JUST HAVE TO.

00:17.542 --> 00:18.667
OF COURSE YOU WILL.

00:18.667 --> 00:21.083
I'M WELL AWARE OF
THE POTTER NEUROSES.

00:21.083 --> 00:22.500
I PREFER TO THINK
OF THEM AS QUIRKS.

00:22.500 --> 00:23.500
DO YOU?

00:23.500 --> 00:25.375
YEAH.

00:25.375 --> 00:27.083
WELL, WHATEVER
WORKS FOR YOU.

00:27.083 --> 00:28.917
I COULD GET INTO
THE LEERY NEUROSES.

00:28.917 --> 00:30.083
UH, WE DON'T HAVE
TO DO THAT.

00:30.083 --> 00:34.083
BESIDES, I'M, UH,
NERVOUS ENOUGH

00:34.083 --> 00:35.542
ON MY OWN RIGHT NOW.

00:35.542 --> 00:37.834
WHY?

00:37.834 --> 00:40.834
UH, WELL, THERE'S A...

00:40.834 --> 00:43.959
THERE'S AN EVENT
LOOMING ON THE HORIZON,

00:43.959 --> 00:45.959
AND, UH...

00:45.959 --> 00:47.542
I SEEM TO RECALL
A CERTAIN PACT

00:47.542 --> 00:50.375
MADE BY
2 HIGH-SCHOOL FRESHMEN
REGARDING SAID EVENT.

00:50.375 --> 00:54.041
JUNIOR PROM.
WE BOTH AGREED IF
WE DIDN'T HAVE DATES,

00:54.041 --> 00:55.542
WE'D GO TOGETHER.

00:55.542 --> 00:56.750
SO YOU DO REMEMBER.

00:58.625 --> 00:59.834
ARE YOU ASKING ME
TO PROM?

00:59.834 --> 01:02.417
I DON'T WANT TO GO
WITH SOME RANDOM PERSON

01:02.417 --> 01:05.000
AND HAVE IT
MEAN NOTHING.

01:05.000 --> 01:08.125
YOU KNOW, I WANT TO GO
WITH MY OLDEST FRIEND.

01:08.125 --> 01:09.166
THAT'LL BE SOMETHING
I'LL ALWAYS REMEMBER.

01:11.834 --> 01:14.291
OR WE CAN BOTH AGREE
THAT IT'S A MEANINGLESS EVENT

01:14.291 --> 01:15.500
AND NOT GO AT ALL.

01:15.500 --> 01:17.166
BUT IT DOES
MEAN SOMETHING.

01:17.166 --> 01:18.708
THERE ARE A MILLION
REASONS WHY PROMS ARE
RIDICULOUS AND STUPID,

01:18.708 --> 01:22.542
BUT WE MADE THAT PACT
BECAUSE IT OBVIOUSLY
MATTERED TO US.

01:22.542 --> 01:24.208
IT'S A RITE OF PASSAGE.

01:24.208 --> 01:26.250
AND I CAN'T THINK OF
ANY BETTER WAY
TO MOVE FORWARD

01:26.250 --> 01:29.417
THAN TO FULFILL A PACT
MADE BY 2 OLD FRIENDS

01:29.417 --> 01:31.166
AND JUST HAVE
A GOOD TIME.

01:32.458 --> 01:34.250
OK.

01:34.250 --> 01:35.834
OK.

01:35.834 --> 01:37.291
BUT I HAVE 2 RULES--

01:37.291 --> 01:38.792
NO CHEESY CORSAGE FOR ME

01:38.792 --> 01:41.750
AND NO BLUE RUFFLEY-
TUXEDOEY-SHIRT-THINGY
FOR YOU.

01:41.750 --> 01:43.250
DONE.

01:44.458 --> 01:45.417
Mitch: THAT'S ONE
FOR RIGHT NOW.

01:45.417 --> 01:48.041
Gale: I HAVE TO GET
TO THE RESTAURANT.

01:48.041 --> 01:49.583
YOU DO NOT.

01:49.583 --> 01:50.750
I HAVE TO GO,
HONEY.

01:54.834 --> 01:56.834
Gale: HONEY. AHEM.

02:49.917 --> 02:51.834
YOU KNOW, I'M NOT
WEARING A WATCH,

02:51.834 --> 02:54.000
BUT I'M PROBABLY
AT LEAST LATE

02:54.000 --> 02:55.166
FOR SOMETHING I SHOULD
PROBABLY BE AT,

02:55.166 --> 02:58.375
SO...I'LL SEE
YOU GUYS LATER.

02:58.375 --> 02:59.917
SEE YA.

02:59.917 --> 03:02.834
UH, SWEETHEART,
WE SHOULD PROBABLY

03:02.834 --> 03:05.125
TALK ABOUT
WHAT YOU JUST SAW.

03:05.125 --> 03:08.000
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'LL TALK TO DAWSON.

03:08.000 --> 03:09.667
YOU SHOULD PROBABLY
GO AHEAD AND GET
TO THE RESTAURANT.

03:09.667 --> 03:11.625
OK.

03:14.250 --> 03:15.583
[KISS]

03:20.333 --> 03:21.375
THIS SHOULD BE GOOD.

03:29.417 --> 03:30.542
YOU OK?

03:30.542 --> 03:31.625
[SNORTS]

03:31.625 --> 03:32.083
YOU KNOW WHAT?

03:32.083 --> 03:35.667
YEAH, I AM.

03:35.667 --> 03:37.375
ABOUT WHAT
YOU JUST SAW--

03:37.375 --> 03:39.041
WHAT I JUST SAW, DAD,
WAS SOMETHING I'VE SEEN

03:39.041 --> 03:41.041
ABOUT 5 MILLION TIMES OVER
THE COURSE OF MY LIFE.

03:41.041 --> 03:43.375
BUT UNDER
THE CIRCUMSTANCES,

03:43.375 --> 03:45.083
DON'T YOU THINK WE
SHOULD TALK ABOUT IT?

03:45.083 --> 03:47.375
[LAUGHS]

03:47.375 --> 03:50.375
DAD, AT THIS POINT,
I'M NUMB.

03:50.375 --> 03:51.708
YOU'RE NUMB?

03:51.708 --> 03:55.250
YEAH. I MEAN,
YOU AND MOM HAVE ALWAYS
HAD A RELATIONSHIP

03:55.250 --> 03:57.542
THAT'S BEEN
A LITTLE DRAMATIC.

03:57.542 --> 03:59.375
ALL THE WHILE,
I'VE BEEN IN THE MIDDLE

03:59.375 --> 04:01.375
THROUGH ALL
THE BACKS-AND-FORTHS
AND UPS AND DOWNS,

04:01.375 --> 04:03.458
AND A LITTLE WHILE AGO
I REALIZED I DON'T
NEED TO DO THAT.

04:03.458 --> 04:09.333
I CAN JUST SIT BACK, DETACHED,
AND WATCH FROM AFAR.

04:09.333 --> 04:10.750
YOU CAN DO THAT.

04:10.750 --> 04:13.250
BUT I THINK
YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT
WHAT'S GOING ON

04:13.250 --> 04:16.750
BETWEEN YOUR MOTHER
AND ME IS A LOT MORE
THAN CASUAL.

04:16.750 --> 04:18.916
ARE YOU SAYING
THAT YOU AND MOM ARE
GETTING BACK TOGETHER?

04:18.916 --> 04:21.333
NO. WE HAVEN'T
DISCUSSED THAT.

04:21.333 --> 04:23.208
OK, DAD, IN THAT CASE,
I WOULD PREFER YOU LEFT ME
OUT OF IT ENTIRELY.

04:23.208 --> 04:25.750
I'M ENJOYING THE NUMBNESS.
YOU HAVEN'T TALKED TO MOM,

04:25.750 --> 04:28.000
YOU DON'T KNOW EVEN
WHAT SHE'S FEELING.

04:28.000 --> 04:31.708
I WAS MARRIED TO
YOUR MOTHER FOR 20 YEARS.

04:31.708 --> 04:34.291
THERE'S SOME THINGS I KNOW
WITHOUT HAVING TO ASK.

04:37.083 --> 04:40.208
HOW'S THE STUDYING
GOING?

04:40.208 --> 04:41.792
FINE.

04:41.792 --> 04:43.792
YOU WANT ANYTHING?
CAN I GET YOU WATER?
LEMONADE?

04:43.792 --> 04:47.000
NO. I'M GOOD.

04:47.000 --> 04:48.500
OK.

04:52.792 --> 04:54.125
UM...

04:54.125 --> 04:57.708
DO YOU...
WANT ME TO GO?

04:58.959 --> 05:00.583
WHY WOULD I
WANT YOU TO GO?

05:01.625 --> 05:03.125
I DON'T KNOW.

05:03.125 --> 05:05.583
I JUST GET
THE FEELING THAT...

05:05.583 --> 05:07.792
I DON'T KNOW.
THAT YOU WANT ME TO GO.

05:09.000 --> 05:10.708
UH-UH. I DON'T
WANT YOU TO GO.

05:10.708 --> 05:12.834
OK.

05:15.250 --> 05:20.625
LOOK, I JUST--
SOMETIMES I...

05:20.625 --> 05:22.875
I JUST FEEL KIND OF...

05:22.875 --> 05:24.458
THIRSTY?

05:24.458 --> 05:26.917
TIRED? MAD? SAD?

05:26.917 --> 05:29.250
YEAH.

05:29.250 --> 05:30.166
SAD?

05:30.166 --> 05:33.125
YEAH. UH, IT'S...

05:33.125 --> 05:36.083
SOMETHING
LIKE THAT. YEAH.

05:36.083 --> 05:38.250
MAYBE IT'S TIME THAT YOU
COME OUT OF THIS CAVE,

05:38.250 --> 05:39.750
JUST GET BACK OUT THERE.

05:39.750 --> 05:41.959
BACK OUT WHERE?

05:41.959 --> 05:45.500
OUT THERE. YOU KNOW,
GO TO THE PROM.

05:45.500 --> 05:47.875
WITH WHO, ANDIE?

05:47.875 --> 05:50.083
I DON'T KNOW.
ANYBODY. A GIRL.

05:50.083 --> 05:52.917
YOU COULD GO WITH ME,
IF YOU WANTED TO.

05:52.917 --> 05:55.166
YOU DON'T HAVE A DATE
TO THE PROM?

05:55.166 --> 05:58.125
I AM CURRENTLY
SIFTING THROUGH OFFERS.

05:58.125 --> 05:59.959
I HAVE JUST YET TO MAKE
MY FINAL DECISION.

06:02.500 --> 06:03.834
DO YOU WANT ME
TO ASK YOU TO THE PROM?

06:03.834 --> 06:07.500
[LAUGHS]

06:07.500 --> 06:09.500
I JUST WANT TO SEE YOU
HAPPY AGAIN.

06:09.500 --> 06:12.041
I DON'T THINK THAT
THE PROM IS GOING TO ACT

06:12.041 --> 06:16.083
AS SOME MAGICAL
HAPPINESS ELIXIR FOR ME.

06:16.083 --> 06:18.041
AND YOU'RE PROBABLY
BETTER OFF

06:18.041 --> 06:20.834
TAKING ONE OF THOSE GUYS
UP ON THEIR OFFER.

06:20.834 --> 06:23.041
I'M SURE I WILL.

06:25.375 --> 06:28.041
DAWSON ASKED ME TO PROM,
AND I SAID YES.

06:29.291 --> 06:32.834
AND NOW I FEEL LIKE I MADE
A HUGE HORRIBLE MISTAKE.

06:32.834 --> 06:35.333
I MEAN, HE ASSURED ME
THAT IT WILL ONLY SERVE

06:35.333 --> 06:37.166
TO RE-CEMENT OUR ADMITTEDLY
SHAKY FRIENDSHIP,

06:37.166 --> 06:38.667
BUT...I DON'T KNOW.

06:38.667 --> 06:41.542
WHAT ABOUT THE UNDENIABLE
ROMANTIC IMPLICATIONS?

06:41.542 --> 06:43.667
NOT TO MENTION PACEY.
WHAT ABOUT PACEY?

06:43.667 --> 06:47.041
WHAT DID YOU THINK
ACCEPTING DAWSON'S
PROM INVITATION WOULD DO

06:47.041 --> 06:50.291
IF NOT PUT YOU RIGHT
IN THE MIDDLE OF HIS
TUG OF WAR WITH PACEY?

06:50.291 --> 06:52.375
[SIGHS]

06:52.375 --> 06:55.000
WELL, I--I KNOW.
I'M JUST--I'M TRYING.

06:55.000 --> 06:58.500
I'M TRYING SO HARD
JUST TO GET THINGS BACK
TO THE WAY THEY WERE.

06:58.500 --> 07:02.417
COME ON, JO.
YOU'RE NOT THAT NAIVE.

07:02.417 --> 07:04.875
I HAVE TO BE.
I'M BACKED UP
INTO A CORNER.

07:04.875 --> 07:06.625
I DON'T HAVE
ANY CHOICE.

07:06.625 --> 07:07.417
YOU ALWAYS
HAVE A CHOICE.

07:07.417 --> 07:11.792
WELL...
NO APPEALING CHOICE.

07:11.792 --> 07:13.333
SO YOU'RE
LOOKING TO ME

07:13.333 --> 07:15.625
TO PROVIDE
THE MAGICAL KEY
TO THIS PROBLEM?

07:15.625 --> 07:16.959
YEAH.

07:16.959 --> 07:18.875
[SIGHS]

07:18.875 --> 07:20.417
I GOTTA SAY,
YOU'VE BEEN A LITTLE THIN

07:20.417 --> 07:21.583
IN THE ADVICE
DEPARTMENT LATELY.

07:21.583 --> 07:25.792
GIVE ME A PROBLEM THAT
ACTUALLY HAS A SOLUTION,

07:25.792 --> 07:27.208
AND I'LL SOLVE IT.

07:29.542 --> 07:31.458
YOU'RE RIGHT.

07:31.458 --> 07:34.500
I MEAN,
NO MATTER WHAT I DO,
SOMEBODY GETS HURT.

07:34.500 --> 07:36.083
INCLUDING ME.

07:39.375 --> 07:41.500
I HATE THE STUPID PROM.

07:41.500 --> 07:44.959
STUPID PROM
CAN KISS MY ASS.

07:44.959 --> 07:46.834
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

07:46.834 --> 07:49.959
I THOUGHT THAT PACEY
WAS GONNA ASK ME
TO THE PROM,

07:49.959 --> 07:54.208
BUT NO, INSTEAD
I MUST HUMILIATE MYSELF
AND GO ALONE.

07:54.208 --> 07:55.291
BETTER YOU THAN GOING
WITH AN EX-BOYFRIEND

07:55.291 --> 07:57.583
THAT YOU'RE
NOT OVER YET.

07:57.583 --> 07:59.959
I AM SO  OVER HIM.

07:59.959 --> 08:02.041
I AM! THAT'S WHY
I WANT TO GO WITH HIM

08:02.041 --> 08:03.875
IS BECAUSE
IT'LL BE SAFE.

08:03.875 --> 08:04.583
MM-HMM.

08:08.875 --> 08:12.041
SO WHAT ABOUT YOU?
DID YOU GET YOUR TICKETS YET?

08:12.041 --> 08:12.959
NO. WORKING ON IT.

08:12.959 --> 08:15.583
SEE, THE THEME
THIS YEAR--COUPLES.

08:15.583 --> 08:17.625
THEY'RE GOING TO HAVE
EVERY COUPLE'S NAMES

08:17.625 --> 08:18.667
ON THE BALLOONS,
THE LITTLE PLACE CARDS,

08:18.667 --> 08:21.667
ON THOSE CHEESY
PROM SOUVENIRS.

08:21.667 --> 08:23.708
SO?

08:23.708 --> 08:25.792
SO WHEN YOU GO
TO BUY YOUR TICKETS,

08:25.792 --> 08:26.917
YOU GOTTA SAY WHO
YOU'RE BRINGING,

08:26.917 --> 08:28.250
WHICH MEANS I HAVE
TO MARCH OVER THERE

08:28.250 --> 08:30.625
AND TELL THE WHOLE WORLD
I'M BRINGING A GUY.

08:30.625 --> 08:33.041
DON'T YOU THINK WHEN
YOU SHOW UP WITH ETHAN,

08:33.041 --> 08:34.833
THEY'RE GONNA FIGURE OUT
THAT HE'S YOUR DATE?

08:34.833 --> 08:37.917
HE'S NOT MY "DATE" DATE.
WE'RE GOING AS FRIENDS.

08:37.917 --> 08:41.500
HE CALLS IT THE NEXT STEP
TOWARDS SELF-ACCEPTANCE
AND ACTUALIZATION,

08:41.500 --> 08:44.000
WHATEVER THE HELL
THAT MEANS.

08:44.000 --> 08:45.667
I DON'T SEE WHAT YOU'RE
SO WORRIED ABOUT.

08:45.667 --> 08:47.333
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU TO CARE
WHAT OTHER PEOPLE THINK.

08:48.208 --> 08:50.125
YOU SEE WHO'S SELLING
THE TICKETS?

08:51.625 --> 08:52.625
BARBARA JOHNS?

08:55.708 --> 08:58.166
SO, YOU KNOW WHAT
THEY'RE HAVING THIS WEEKEND

08:58.166 --> 09:00.834
IS THE JUNIOR PROM.

09:00.834 --> 09:01.792
REALLY?

09:01.792 --> 09:03.708
YEAH. GOD, IS THERE
A MORE RIDICULOUS

09:03.708 --> 09:05.959
AND EMBARRASSING RITUAL
THAN THE PROM?

09:05.959 --> 09:09.041
THE WAY THAT IT TOTALLY
REINFORCES TRADITIONAL
GENDER ROLES,

09:09.041 --> 09:11.166
REWARDS THE COOL KIDS,
PUNISHES THE GEEKS,

09:11.166 --> 09:14.208
I MEAN, THE PRESSURE
THIS ONE SINGLE NIGHT

09:14.208 --> 09:16.000
EXERTS ON
THE COMMON TEENAGER...

09:16.000 --> 09:17.959
TO MAKE HOLLOW, AWKWARD
ROMANTIC GESTURES

09:17.959 --> 09:19.834
LIKE PINNING
A CHEAP CORSAGE
ON TAFFETA,

09:19.834 --> 09:22.458
HAVING DRUNKEN SEX
WITH SOME GUY WHOSE NAME
YOU WON'T REMEMBER,

09:22.458 --> 09:25.000
AND THEN PUKING
IN THE BACK OF SOME
CHEESY-ASS RENTED LIMO,

09:25.000 --> 09:27.208
I MEAN, IT'S JUST
SO OVERWHELMING.

09:27.208 --> 09:29.792
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN TO
A PROM BEFORE, HAVE YOU?

09:31.542 --> 09:34.542
WELL, NO. BUT I KNOW
ENOUGH ABOUT THEM
TO KNOW IT'S A SAD--

09:34.542 --> 09:36.834
SO, IN OTHER WORDS,
YOU'RE ASKING ME TO GO.

09:36.834 --> 09:38.750
[SIGHS]

09:39.125 --> 09:41.375
YEAH.

09:41.375 --> 09:42.917
I'D LOVE TO.

09:44.917 --> 09:45.875
OK.

09:47.333 --> 09:49.083
Barbara: THE THEME
OF THIS YEAR'S PROM
IS "COUPLES."

09:49.083 --> 09:51.875
PLEASE STATE YOUR NAME
AS WELL AS THE NAME
OF YOUR DATE.

09:51.875 --> 09:55.333
AHEM. YEAH.
IT'S, UM, JACK McPHEE...

09:55.333 --> 09:59.208
AND, UM, ETHAN BRODY.

09:59.208 --> 09:59.917
EXCUSE ME?

09:59.917 --> 10:02.083
ETHAN BRODY.
E-T-H-A-N.

10:02.083 --> 10:03.583
NO, NO, NO.

10:03.583 --> 10:04.917
A BOY CANNOT GO TO
THE PROM WITH A BOY.

10:04.917 --> 10:06.834
THE DEFINITION OF A PROM DATE
IS A BOY AND A GIRL.

10:06.834 --> 10:09.125
WELL, I DON'T THINK
THAT'S ANY OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

10:09.125 --> 10:12.417
TO BE HONEST,
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU FEEL THE NEED

10:12.417 --> 10:15.333
TO CAUSE A SPECTACLE
AND RUIN THE PROM
FOR THE REST OF US,

10:15.333 --> 10:16.417
BUT IF YOU FEEL
YOU HAVE TO DO SO,

10:16.417 --> 10:18.708
I CAN'T SELL YOU A TICKET

10:18.708 --> 10:21.083
TILL I TALK TO MRS. MEYER,
HEAD OF THE PROM COMMITTEE.

10:21.083 --> 10:22.750
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
SELL ME A TICKET?

10:22.750 --> 10:23.959
WHAT EXACTLY IS IT
THE TWO OF YOU
WILL DO, ANYWAY?

10:23.959 --> 10:27.625
TAKE A NICE PROM PHOTO
FOR GRANDMA'S PHOTO ALBUM?

10:27.625 --> 10:30.834
DANCE STUBBLED CHEEK
TO STUBBLED CHEEK?

10:30.834 --> 10:32.667
SHARE A ROMANTIC KISS
UNDER THE MOONLIGHT?

10:32.667 --> 10:34.792
YOU DON'T THINK
THAT'S GONNA WEIRD OUT

10:34.792 --> 10:35.417
EVEN THE ONES
WHO ARE SYMPATHETIC
TO PEOPLE LIKE YOU?

10:35.417 --> 10:36.875
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

10:36.875 --> 10:38.708
LIKE I SAID, JACK,
I'LL CHECK WITH MRS. MEYER,

10:38.708 --> 10:41.667
AND YOU CAN COME BACK
AND TRY AGAIN.

10:41.667 --> 10:41.875
NEXT!

10:44.208 --> 10:45.583
WHAT'S UP, JACK?
YOU OK?

10:45.583 --> 10:48.625
YEAH, YEAH,
I'M FINE.

10:48.625 --> 10:50.083
I--I GOTTA GO.

10:52.667 --> 10:54.792
THE THEME OF THIS YEAR'S
PROM IS "COUPLES."

10:54.792 --> 10:57.917
PLEASE STATE
YOUR NAME AS WELL AS
THE NAME OF YOUR DATE.

10:57.917 --> 11:00.333
BARBARA,
YOU'RE IN MY GYM CLASS.
YOU KNOW MY NAME.

11:00.333 --> 11:02.959
PLEASE STATE YOUR NAME
AS WELL AS THE NAME
OF YOUR DATE.

11:02.959 --> 11:04.667
DAWSON LEERY
AND JOEY POTTER.

11:04.667 --> 11:07.625
OH? HAPPY COUPLE
BACK TOGETHER?

11:07.625 --> 11:10.542
SOMETHING LIKE THAT,
YEAH.

11:25.291 --> 11:27.542
THEY CAN'T DO THIS
TO YOU JACK.
WE WON'T LET THEM.

11:27.542 --> 11:30.875
YEAH. WE'LL--WE'LL LODGE
A FORMAL COMPLAINT.

11:30.875 --> 11:33.917
NOT ONLY WILL YOU GET
YOUR TICKETS FOR FREE,

11:33.917 --> 11:36.000
BUT WE WILL GET
BARBARA JOHNS
TO APOLOGIZE

11:36.000 --> 11:36.667
IN FRONT OF
THE WHOLE SCHOOL.

11:36.667 --> 11:38.750
ON HER HANDS
AND KNEES.

11:38.750 --> 11:40.083
GUYS...

11:40.083 --> 11:41.917
WE COULD GO TO MRS. MEYER
AND TELL HER WHAT BARBARA DID.

11:41.917 --> 11:45.583
SHE HAS TO
SELL THE TICKETS.
IT'S DISCRIMINATION.

11:45.583 --> 11:46.708
GUYS!

11:46.708 --> 11:49.708
I APPRECIATE
THE SUPPORT, I DO,

11:49.708 --> 11:51.708
BUT IT'S OK.
I'M JUST NOT GONNA
GO TO THE PROM.

11:51.708 --> 11:53.625
WHAT?
YOU HAVE TO GO!

11:53.625 --> 11:55.625
AT THIS POINT,
IT'S POLITICAL.

11:55.625 --> 11:58.625
THAT'S JUST IT. IT'S A PROM.
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE FUN.

11:58.625 --> 12:00.291
WHY DOES MY ENTIRE LIFE
HAVE TO BE A FIGHT?

12:00.291 --> 12:02.542
WHY IS SOMETHING THAT'S
NORMAL FOR SOMEONE ELSE

12:02.542 --> 12:03.917
HAVE TO BE
SO POLITICAL FOR ME?

12:03.917 --> 12:05.667
'CAUSE THAT'S JUST
THE WAY IT IS,

12:05.667 --> 12:08.125
AND UNTIL THINGS CHANGE,
YOU HAVE TO FIGHT.

12:08.125 --> 12:09.959
AND WE'LL BE
THERE WITH YOU.
ALL THE WAY.

12:11.792 --> 12:13.375
JUST WANTED TO
GO TO THE PROM.

12:13.375 --> 12:15.625
THAT'S ALL.

12:15.625 --> 12:16.208
WELL, IF YOU'RE NOT GOING,
I'M NOT GOING.

12:16.208 --> 12:18.625
ME, NEITHER.

12:18.625 --> 12:22.959
Andie: GOOD!
THEN WE'LL BOYCOTT,
AND WE'LL ORGANIZE.

12:22.959 --> 12:26.375
I'VE GOT A BETTER IDEA.
JACK, YOU'RE RIGHT.

12:26.375 --> 12:27.708
LET'S HOLD OUR OWN PROM.

12:27.708 --> 12:29.083
