24:52.708 --> 24:55.750
COULD I ASK A BRAZEN
BUT OBVIOUS QUESTION?

24:55.750 --> 24:59.583
YEAH, OF COURSE.

24:59.583 --> 25:01.166
WHY DID YOU
BRING ME HERE
TONIGHT, DAWSON?

25:01.166 --> 25:02.375
WHAT?

25:02.375 --> 25:06.000
WAS IT JUST SO YOU
COULD THROW JABS
AT PACEY?

25:06.000 --> 25:07.041
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

25:07.041 --> 25:09.417
I HAD NO IDEA PACEY
WOULD BE HERE.

25:09.417 --> 25:10.500
YOU DON'T THINK
I GET THE SUBTEXT

25:10.500 --> 25:11.500
OF EVERY ONE
OF THOSE LOOKS

25:11.500 --> 25:12.708
YOU KEEP THROWING
HIS WAY?

25:12.708 --> 25:15.166
I MEAN, DAWSON,
YOU MIGHT AS WELL
GET ON THE P.A.

25:15.166 --> 25:18.959
AND SCREAM,
"SHE'S MINE, PACEY.
HA. I WIN."

25:18.959 --> 25:20.333
ACTUALLY, THAT'S NOT
WHAT I'M THINKING.

25:20.333 --> 25:22.875
THEN WHAT ARE
YOU THINKING?

25:22.875 --> 25:24.542
I'M THINKING,
WHAT RIGHT
DID HE HAVE

25:24.542 --> 25:26.083
TO SHOW UP
TO MY MOTHER'S
RESTAURANT

25:26.083 --> 25:27.208
AT A PROM THAT
I ORGANIZED.

25:27.208 --> 25:29.208
WHAT EXACTLY
IS HE TRYING
TO ACCOMPLISH?

25:29.208 --> 25:30.708
NOW, GIVEN
THE CIRCUMSTANCES

25:30.708 --> 25:32.000
UNDER WHICH
THIS NIGHT ORIGINATED,

25:32.000 --> 25:33.375
WHAT RIGHT DO YOU HAVE
TO EXCLUDE ANYONE?

25:33.375 --> 25:34.333
I'M NOT
EXCLUDING HIM, JO.

25:34.333 --> 25:35.417
I HAVEN'T SAID
A WORD TO HIM.

25:35.417 --> 25:37.500
FINE, BUT THAT
HASN'T STOPPED YOU

25:37.500 --> 25:38.834
FROM PARADING ME
AROUND ALL NIGHT

25:38.834 --> 25:40.291
LIKE I'M SOME SORT
OF A PRIZE.

25:40.291 --> 25:42.583
PARADING YOU?
I'M NOT PARADING YOU
AROUND, JOEY.

25:42.583 --> 25:44.083
YOU'RE MY DATE,
AND I'M DANCING WITH YOU.

25:44.083 --> 25:46.375
IT'S NOT MY FAULT
IF THEY KEEP
STARING AT US.

25:46.375 --> 25:49.875
YOU'RE RIGHT.
NONE OF IT'S
YOUR FAULT.

25:49.875 --> 25:50.959
NONE OF IT'S
ANYBODY'S FAULT.

25:50.959 --> 25:52.417
IT'S JUST
HAPPENING.

25:52.417 --> 25:54.875
AND WHO CARES
WHAT IT'S DOING
TO ME?

25:54.875 --> 25:57.834
OK.

26:00.333 --> 26:03.667
YOU KNOW, LET'S JUST
START OVER, OK?

26:03.667 --> 26:06.792
IT'S JUST DAWSON
AND JOEY AT THE PROM

26:06.792 --> 26:11.834
HAVING A GOOD TIME.
OK?

26:16.208 --> 26:17.750
I NEED A BREATHER.

26:37.667 --> 26:39.458
CARE TO MAKE
A RUN FOR IT?

26:39.458 --> 26:41.458
YES, PLEASE.

26:41.458 --> 26:42.667
OHH.

26:46.625 --> 26:49.333
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
HIDING FROM?

26:49.333 --> 26:51.792
I AM HIDING
FROM BARBARA JOHNS.

26:51.792 --> 26:53.291
SHE'S HERE?

26:53.291 --> 26:56.417
NO. YEAH,
IN A WAY, SHE IS.

26:59.041 --> 27:02.083
OH, MAN.
SHE WAS RIGHT, JOEY.

27:02.083 --> 27:03.708
YOU KNOW,
I DON'T BELONG HERE.

27:03.708 --> 27:05.208
I'M NOT GONNA DANCE
WITH ETHAN.

27:05.208 --> 27:07.291
I'M NOT GONNA
HAVE MY PICTURE
TAKEN WITH HIM.

27:07.291 --> 27:09.792
AND WHATEVER
GOOD TIME I WAS
GONNA HAVE TONIGHT,

27:09.792 --> 27:12.166
I JUST RUINED IT
BY THE WAY
I TREATED HIM.

27:14.291 --> 27:17.291
YOU REALLY LIKE HIM,
DON'T YOU?

27:17.291 --> 27:18.959
I REMEMBER
A CONVERSATION

27:18.959 --> 27:21.041
LESS THAN
A YEAR AGO,

27:21.041 --> 27:23.458
UNDER THESE
VERY STARS,

27:23.458 --> 27:25.458
AND ALL
YOU COULD SEE

27:25.458 --> 27:27.917
WAS THE PAIN
AND THE LONELINESS

27:27.917 --> 27:31.250
THAT MADE YOUR LIFE
DIFFERENT FROM
EVERYONE ELSE'S.

27:31.250 --> 27:34.333
AS OPPOSED TO NOW,
WHEN ALL I CAN SEE

27:34.333 --> 27:35.166
IS THE PAIN
AND LONELINESS

27:35.166 --> 27:36.750
THAT MAKES
OUR LIVES THE SAME?

27:42.375 --> 27:43.917
LOOK. I KNOW HOW SAD
IT IS TO HIDE

27:43.917 --> 27:45.875
FROM SOMETHING
THAT YOU REALLY WANT, JOEY.

27:45.875 --> 27:47.125
I JUST WANT
EVERYTHING
TO GO BACK

27:47.125 --> 27:48.500
TO THE WAY
IT WAS, YOU KNOW?

27:48.500 --> 27:49.917
ALL OF US
FRIENDS AGAIN,

27:49.917 --> 27:53.000
AND--AND ME
NOT CAUGHT
IN THE MIDDLE.

27:53.000 --> 27:56.000
WELL, IF YOU WANT THINGS
TO GET BACK TO THE WAY
THAT THEY WERE,

27:56.000 --> 27:59.166
YOU HAVE TO SET
THE EXAMPLE.

27:59.166 --> 28:00.500
DAWSON AND PACEY,
THOSE TWO

28:00.500 --> 28:02.750
JUST AREN'T GONNA DO IT
THEMSELVES RIGHT NOW.

28:05.333 --> 28:07.708
HOW ABOUT
WE HIDE OUT HERE
FOR A WHILE FIRST?

28:07.708 --> 28:11.875
IT SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

28:16.083 --> 28:17.166
THANK YOU.

28:17.166 --> 28:18.583
THANK YOU.

28:18.583 --> 28:19.708
YOU KNOW, THIS MIGHT
BE A TAD PRESUMPTUOUS,

28:19.708 --> 28:22.667
BUT I TOOK THE LIBERTY
OF PACKING A BAG.

28:22.667 --> 28:24.834
I THOUGHT MAYBE
I COULD STAY OVER.

28:24.834 --> 28:28.708
I'M NOT SURE
THAT'S SUCH
A GOOD IDEA, GALE.

28:28.708 --> 28:31.083
MITCHELL,
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

28:31.083 --> 28:34.208
I'M NOT HERE JUST
FOR YOUR WHIM, GALE.

28:34.208 --> 28:36.000
[LAUGHS]
EXCUSE ME?

28:36.000 --> 28:37.291
GO AHEAD AND LAUGH,
BUT YOU KNOW,

28:37.291 --> 28:38.333
WE'VE FINALLY
GOTTEN BACK

28:38.333 --> 28:39.208
TO THIS POINT
IN OUR RELATIONSHIP

28:39.208 --> 28:40.875
BY BEING HONEST
WITH EACH OTHER.

28:40.875 --> 28:44.542
I'M NOT GONNA STOP
THAT HONESTY NOW.

28:44.542 --> 28:49.250
OK. SO IF
THE HONEST THING
IS TO TALK ABOUT IT,

28:49.250 --> 28:50.708
LET'S TALK
ABOUT IT.

28:50.708 --> 28:52.959
I CAN'T KEEP
PLAYING THIS GAME.

28:52.959 --> 28:56.500
IS IT A SLIP-UP?
IS IT A RELATIONSHIP?

28:56.500 --> 28:59.000
IS IT A SATURDAY-NIGHT
ARRANGEMENT? WHAT IS IT?

28:59.000 --> 29:00.166
WHAT DO YOU
WANT IT TO BE?

29:00.166 --> 29:01.333
NAH.

29:01.333 --> 29:02.875
YOU KNOW WHAT, GALE?
I'M SICK OF
BEING THE ONE

29:02.875 --> 29:05.667
ALWAYS
ANXIOUS TO DEFINE
OUR RELATIONSHIP

29:05.667 --> 29:07.834
OR LACK THEREOF.

29:07.834 --> 29:08.875
WHAT I WANT IS
FOR YOU TO DEFINE
IT FOR ONCE.

29:20.500 --> 29:23.208
I'VE BEEN MEANING
TO ASK YOU SOMETHING
ALL NIGHT, PACEY.

29:26.792 --> 29:28.041
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO DANCE WITH ME?

29:32.250 --> 29:33.041
YES.

29:47.083 --> 29:50.917
HOW COME THIS FEELS
SO RIGHT?

29:50.917 --> 29:52.959
I THINK IT WAS
THOSE DANCE LESSONS.

30:04.542 --> 30:06.375
WHERE DID YOU GET THOSE?

30:06.375 --> 30:09.000
THEY'RE NOT YOU.

30:09.000 --> 30:11.708
WHY, BECAUSE
I'M JUST
A POOR TOMBOY,

30:11.708 --> 30:16.500
OR 'CAUSE DAWSON
GAVE THEM TO ME?

30:18.583 --> 30:20.125
NEITHER.

30:20.125 --> 30:23.792
YOU SEE THIS?

30:23.792 --> 30:25.792
THIS IS YOU.

30:25.792 --> 30:30.458
IT'S NOT SHOWY
OR GAUDY.

30:30.458 --> 30:34.250
JUST SIMPLE.

30:34.250 --> 30:36.333
ELEGANT.

30:36.333 --> 30:40.333
BEAUTIFUL.

30:40.333 --> 30:42.875
IT'S MY MOM'S BRACELET.

30:45.375 --> 30:46.583
I KNOW.

30:49.375 --> 30:51.750
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

30:51.750 --> 30:54.917
WELL, BECAUSE
YOU TOLD ME.

30:54.917 --> 30:56.000
6 MONTHS AGO.

30:56.000 --> 30:59.917
YOU WERE WEARING
THAT, UH,
BLUE SWEATER

30:59.917 --> 31:02.792
WITH THE SNOWFLAKES
THAT YOU HAVE.

31:02.792 --> 31:03.834
WE WERE WALKING DOWN
THE HALLWAYS AT SCHOOL.

31:03.834 --> 31:08.166
I WAS ANNOYING YOU
AS PER USUAL.

31:08.166 --> 31:09.625
YOU SAID, "LOOK, PACEY.

31:09.625 --> 31:11.500
"I JUST FOUND
MY MOTHER'S BRACELET
THIS MORNING,

31:11.500 --> 31:14.291
SO WHY DON'T YOU
CUT ME SOME SLACK?"

31:16.583 --> 31:19.875
YOU REMEMBER THAT?

31:21.834 --> 31:24.917
I REMEMBER
EVERYTHING.

32:06.291 --> 32:07.583
DAWSON.

32:07.583 --> 32:10.291
DAWSON, WAIT.

32:10.291 --> 32:12.917
DAWSON, WAIT.

32:12.917 --> 32:13.750
HOW COULD YOU
DO THAT TO ME?

32:13.750 --> 32:14.834
ARE YOU TRYING
TO HURT ME?

32:14.834 --> 32:16.959
NO! I'M TRYING
TO SET AN EXAMPLE.

32:16.959 --> 32:18.959
I'M TRYING TO GET
THINGS BACK

32:18.959 --> 32:20.083
TO THE WAY
THEY WERE.

32:20.083 --> 32:21.667
YOU CAN'T GO BACK
TO THE WAY THEY WERE, JOEY.

32:21.667 --> 32:22.834
DON'T YOU GET IT?

32:22.834 --> 32:24.542
YOU CAN'T CLIMB
THROUGH MY WINDOW,

32:24.542 --> 32:26.417
POP IN E.T.,  AND HAVE IT
BE THE SAME, OK?

32:26.417 --> 32:27.834
YOU CAN'T DANCE
WITH HIM

32:27.834 --> 32:28.792
AT THE PROM
I ORGANIZED

32:28.792 --> 32:30.417
AND EXPECT ME
NOT TO BE HURT.

32:30.417 --> 32:32.875
YOU SAID TONIGHT
WAS ABOUT YOU, ME,
AND OUR FRIENDSHIP.

32:32.875 --> 32:34.375
AND IF THAT WAS
REALLY THE CASE,

32:34.375 --> 32:35.583
IT WOULDN'T MATTER
WHO I DANCED WITH.

32:35.583 --> 32:36.583
I SAID TONIGHT
WAS ABOUT MOVING
FORWARD, JOEY.

32:36.583 --> 32:38.083
WHAT DID YOU THINK
THAT MEANT?

32:38.083 --> 32:42.500
YOU CAN'T HAVE THOUGHT
THAT THAT'S ALL I WANTED.

32:42.500 --> 32:43.542
THE WHOLE REASON
I SUGGESTED

32:43.542 --> 32:45.500
THIS WHOLE STUPID
ALTERNATIVE PROM

32:45.500 --> 32:47.625
WASN'T ABOUT JACK,
IT WAS ABOUT YOU,
ALL RIGHT?

32:47.625 --> 32:49.125
AND MAYBE
I TRIED TOO HARD,

32:49.125 --> 32:50.750
BUT I DIDN'T WANT
TO MISS MY CHANCE
TO DANCE WITH YOU,

32:50.750 --> 32:53.500
TO HOLD YOU, TO MAKE YOU
REMEMBER WHAT IT WAS LIKE
BETWEEN US.

32:53.500 --> 32:58.458
I THOUGHT MAYBE, YOU KNOW,
IF I COULD MAKE IT PERFECT...

33:00.834 --> 33:02.750
THAT I WOULD
PICK YOU?

33:02.750 --> 33:05.417
SAY IT, DAWSON.

33:05.417 --> 33:07.500
YOU THOUGHT
IF YOU ORCHESTRATED
THIS WHOLE EVENING,

33:07.500 --> 33:08.750
THAT I WOULD
BE CONVINCED

33:08.750 --> 33:10.208
INTO PICKING YOU
OVER PACEY, RIGHT?

33:10.208 --> 33:13.792
YOU HAVE TO PICK
SOMEBODY, JOEY.

33:13.792 --> 33:14.959
I JUST WANTED
TO REMIND YOU

33:14.959 --> 33:16.542
WHAT YOU'D BE MISSING
IF YOU DIDN'T PICK ME.

33:18.959 --> 33:22.166
'CAUSE YOU'D BE
MISSING A LOT.

33:22.166 --> 33:25.000
SO WOULD I.
WE'D BE MISSING EVERYTHING.

33:46.667 --> 33:50.917
THAT'S HOW THE EVENING
WAS SUPPOSED TO END.

33:59.250 --> 34:02.250
I THINK I CAN TAKE IT
FROM HERE, THANKS.

34:02.250 --> 34:05.708
WOW, I THINK THOSE
WERE THE MOST WORDS
YOU'VE SAID TO ME

34:05.708 --> 34:07.208
SINCE I TOLD YOU
ABOUT FOOTBALL CAMP.

34:07.208 --> 34:08.917
HENRY, I'M NOT
IN THE MOOD.

34:08.917 --> 34:12.583
FINE. THEN,
LET'S TALK ABOUT
SOMETHING ELSE,

34:12.583 --> 34:14.417
LIKE WHY WOULD YOU
MAKE SUCH A BIG DEAL

34:14.417 --> 34:16.875
ABOUT THERE BEING
NO POSSIBILITY
OF US HAVING SEX

34:16.875 --> 34:18.625
IF YOU WERE PLANNING
TO DO IT ALL ALONG?

34:18.625 --> 34:20.542
I WASN'T PLANNING
ON ANYTHING.

34:20.542 --> 34:24.875
I MEAN, I THOUGHT THAT--
THAT MAYBE IF IT HAPPENED,
IF IT FELT RIGHT AND--

34:24.875 --> 34:27.583
AND NATURAL, THEN YEAH,
MAYBE WE WOULD, BUT YOU KNOW,
IT DOESN'T EVEN MATTER.

34:27.583 --> 34:29.708
BECAUSE OF
FOOTBALL CAMP?

34:29.708 --> 34:31.208
YOU KNOW, I HATE IT
WHEN YOU DO THIS.

34:31.208 --> 34:33.458
YOU GET EXTREME
ABOUT THE FUTURE
OF OUR RELATIONSHIP

34:33.458 --> 34:35.708
AT THE FIRST SIGN
OF ONE OF YOUR
INSECURITIES.

34:35.708 --> 34:37.708
THIS ISN'T ABOUT
MY INSECURITIES, HENRY.

34:37.708 --> 34:38.708
IT'S ABOUT
YOUR COWARDICE,

34:38.708 --> 34:40.667
WHAT?
AND THE FACT
THAT I PLANNED

34:40.667 --> 34:41.500
OUR ENTIRE
SUMMER TOGETHER,

34:41.500 --> 34:42.375
AND YOU WEREN'T
EVEN THINKING

34:42.375 --> 34:43.917
ABOUT SPENDING
ANY TIME WITH ME.

34:43.917 --> 34:49.875
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN MY LIFE, I MADE MYSELF
VULNERABLE TO SOMEBODY...

34:49.875 --> 34:51.333
AND NOW I JUST FEEL STUPID.

34:51.333 --> 34:55.166
JEN, MY DECISION
TO GO, IT'S--

34:55.166 --> 34:55.750
IT'S GOT NOTHING
TO DO WITH YOU.

34:55.750 --> 34:57.583
EXACTLY.

34:57.583 --> 34:59.458
BUT IF THIS WERE
A REAL RELATIONSHIP,

34:59.458 --> 35:00.750
YOUR CHOICE
FOR THOSE 8 WEEKS,

35:00.750 --> 35:02.875
IT WOULD HAVE HAD
AT LEAST SOMETHING
TO DO WITH ME.

35:05.083 --> 35:07.083
GOOD NIGHT, HENRY.

35:07.083 --> 35:09.917
JEN, I WON'T GO
THROUGH THIS AGAIN.
I CAN'T.

35:09.917 --> 35:11.208
THIS TIME,
THERE WON'T BE
ANY POSTERS

35:11.208 --> 35:13.208
OR GRAND
DECLARATIONS
OF MY FEELINGS

35:13.208 --> 35:16.750
TOWARDS YOU.
YOU WALK
IN THAT HOUSE,

35:16.750 --> 35:18.834
AND IT'S NOT JUST
GOOD NIGHT...

35:18.834 --> 35:21.250
IT'S GOOD-BYE.

35:24.750 --> 35:26.250
GOOD-BYE.

35:29.750 --> 35:31.792
ETHAN, WAIT!

35:31.792 --> 35:33.000
WAIT.

35:34.208 --> 35:35.708
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
ARE YOU LEAVING?

35:35.708 --> 35:37.166
ARE YOU
KIDDING ME?

35:38.417 --> 35:41.875
LOOK, I-I'M SORRY
FOR THE WAY THAT
I ACTED TONIGHT.

35:41.875 --> 35:42.792
NO, JACK, I'M  SORRY.

35:42.792 --> 35:45.041
YOU CLEARLY WEREN'T
READY FOR THIS.

35:46.875 --> 35:51.291
THAT'S JUST IT,
BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THIS  IS,

35:51.291 --> 35:53.333
SO MAYBE WE SHOULD
DEFINE THIS  BEFORE
WE DECIDE WHO'S READY.

36:00.542 --> 36:01.667
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

36:03.208 --> 36:04.333
I-I'M SAYING...

36:07.792 --> 36:11.333
OK, I'M SAYING
THAT TONIGHT...

36:11.333 --> 36:12.750
I DON'T THINK THAT
I WAS UNCOMFORTABLE

36:12.750 --> 36:14.166
WITH BRINGING
A GUY TO THE PROM.

36:15.333 --> 36:17.166
I THINK I WAS
UNCOMFORTABLE
WITH TAKING SOMEONE

36:17.166 --> 36:19.834
THAT DOESN'T FEEL
THE SAME WAY ABOUT ME
AS I FEEL ABOUT HIM.

36:19.834 --> 36:23.125
JACK,
I REALLY  LIKE YOU.

36:23.125 --> 36:25.583
THEN WHY
ALL THE HURDLES?

36:25.583 --> 36:27.417
WHY THIS WHOLE JOURNEY
FOR US TO BE TOGETHER

36:27.417 --> 36:30.500
WHEN ALL YOU HAD TO DO
WAS JUST LEAN OVER AND--

36:30.500 --> 36:32.000
KISS YOU.

36:33.291 --> 36:35.000
YEAH,
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

36:35.000 --> 36:37.375
BECAUSE, JACK,
I DON'T WANNA
KISS SOMEONE

36:37.375 --> 36:39.834
WHO ISN'T READY.
AND I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'RE READY,

36:39.834 --> 36:41.166
SO I'M AFRAID--

36:41.166 --> 36:44.041
YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO KISS
ME FIRST.

36:44.041 --> 36:46.000
HOW DO YOU KNOW
THAT I COULDN'T?

36:46.000 --> 36:49.291
I DON'T KNOW.
I'M GUESSING.

36:49.291 --> 36:53.083
THEN MAYBE
YOU'RE GUESSING WRONG.
MAYBE I AM READY.

36:53.083 --> 36:56.917
OK, SO HERE
WE ARE--A LONE
TRAIN STATION,

36:56.917 --> 37:01.333
NO ONE AROUND,
NO LIGHTS,
NO CAMERAS,

37:01.333 --> 37:03.250
NO NETWORK
TELEVISION

37:03.250 --> 37:05.166
TO CUT
TO COMMERCIAL.

37:05.166 --> 37:06.875
IT'S JUST
YOU AND ME.

37:08.417 --> 37:11.208
SO KISS ME, JACK.

37:11.208 --> 37:12.625
I DARE YOU.

37:31.375 --> 37:34.083
I HONESTLY BELIEVED

37:34.083 --> 37:36.834
THAT WHEN I CAME OVER
TO INVITE YOU TO THE PROM,

37:36.834 --> 37:40.375
IT WAS BECAUSE I WANTED
TO GO TO THE PROM WITH YOU,

37:40.375 --> 37:45.000
AND I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW MUCH
I WISH THAT WERE THE TRUTH,

37:45.000 --> 37:49.458
BUT AS SOON AS I GOT THERE,

37:49.458 --> 37:52.500
I REALIZED THAT I WANTED
TO GO TO THE PROM BECAUSE--

37:52.500 --> 37:56.959
I KNOW WHY YOU
WANTED TO GO TO
THE PROM, PACEY,

37:56.959 --> 37:59.625
AND I'M SORRY
THAT IT DIDN'T
WORK OUT FOR YOU.

38:01.250 --> 38:04.250
BUT AT LEAST YOU GOT
TO DANCE WITH HER.

38:04.250 --> 38:06.250
WHAT CAN I DO?

38:06.250 --> 38:08.166
REALLY, I WOULD DO
WHATEVER IT TAKES

38:08.166 --> 38:10.500
TO MAKE THIS
UP TO YOU, ANDIE.

38:11.417 --> 38:13.583
WHAT IT WOULD TAKE
IS SOMETHING THAT

38:13.583 --> 38:15.417
I DON'T THINK YOU CAN
GIVE ME RIGHT NOW,

38:15.417 --> 38:17.917
AND I'M NOT MAD
AT YOU, PACEY--

38:17.917 --> 38:19.959
HONESTLY, I'M NOT.
I JUST--

38:19.959 --> 38:23.083
I JUST REALLY
FEEL BAD FOR YOU.

38:34.667 --> 38:39.208
DID I TELL YOU
WHAT I'M GONNA BE
DOING THIS SUMMER?

38:39.208 --> 38:41.458
I'M GONNA SAIL TRUE LOVE
DOWN TO KEY WEST.

38:44.917 --> 38:46.333
JUST ME AND THE SEA.

38:46.333 --> 38:50.291
HOW'S THAT
FOR HEMINGWAYESQUE, HUH?

38:52.500 --> 38:55.875
SO WHEN ARE YOU
GONNA LEAVE?

38:55.875 --> 38:57.583
RIGHT AFTER FINALS.

39:00.875 --> 39:04.583
HAVE YOU TOLD HER
HOW YOU FEEL?

39:04.583 --> 39:07.625
ANDIE, SHE ALREADY
KNOWS HOW I FEEL.

39:11.333 --> 39:12.667
I MEAN,
HAVE YOU REALLY
TOLD HER, PACEY?

39:16.500 --> 39:19.333
YOU CAN'T JUST
LEAVE WITHOUT
LETTING HER KNOW.

39:19.333 --> 39:21.417
I MEAN, THAT'S
NOT LIKE YOU.

39:21.417 --> 39:24.125
YOU--YOU DON'T
JUST STAND AND
LET THINGS HAPPEN,

39:24.125 --> 39:25.792
AND YOU DON'T
RUN AWAY, EITHER.

39:25.792 --> 39:29.417
YOU HAVE TO TELL HER
THAT YOU LOVE HER,

39:29.417 --> 39:33.208
AND YOU HAVE TO TRY
TO GET HER BACK,

39:33.208 --> 39:34.583
BECAUSE IF
YOU DON'T,

39:34.583 --> 39:37.500
I PROMISE YOU,
YOU WILL REGRET IT.

39:40.750 --> 39:41.834
MAYBE.

39:41.834 --> 39:42.959
NO, PACEY,

39:42.959 --> 39:45.458
YOU WILL.

39:56.959 --> 39:59.667
HEY.

40:00.708 --> 40:01.834
HEY.

40:01.834 --> 40:05.041
UM...

40:05.041 --> 40:08.875
I BROUGHT THESE
BACK FOR YOU.

40:08.875 --> 40:11.291
THEY'RE
SO BEAUTIFUL, I--

40:11.291 --> 40:14.208
I'M NOT QUITE SURE
THEY'RE ME, BUT...

40:14.208 --> 40:16.625
REALLY FUN TIME
WEARING THEM.

40:18.834 --> 40:24.625
SO, I'M NOT GOING TO DENY THAT
WHEN YOU KISSED ME LAST NIGHT...

40:24.625 --> 40:26.667
I FELT SOMETHING.

40:28.792 --> 40:31.417
SOMETHING THAT I
WASN'T EXPECTING,
AND SOMETHING THAT...

40:31.417 --> 40:34.708
PROBABLY WILL
ALWAYS BE THERE.

40:38.542 --> 40:42.333
I CAN'T KEEP
HURTING PEOPLE, DAWSON,

40:42.333 --> 40:46.792
AND I CAN'T CHOOSE,

40:46.792 --> 40:51.500
SO I'M TELLING YOU
THE SAME THING
THAT I TOLD PACEY.

40:53.125 --> 40:55.375
PLEASE DON'T MAKE ME.

40:55.375 --> 40:58.917
I'M NOT READY,
AND I CAN'T DO IT.

41:03.333 --> 41:04.959
OK.

41:04.959 --> 41:06.041
OK?

41:06.041 --> 41:07.959
I'LL WAIT.

41:07.959 --> 41:10.250
YOU CAN CALL ME
AN ETERNAL OPTIMIST,

41:10.250 --> 41:13.250
BUT I HAVE FAITH.

41:16.792 --> 41:19.166
THIS WHOLE YEAR,
I'VE BEEN ON THIS...

41:19.166 --> 41:21.291
SOUL-SEARCHING
JOURNEY...

41:24.166 --> 41:25.708
AND I FEEL LIKE
I'VE FINALLY COME
TO THE END.

41:29.083 --> 41:32.000
AND WHAT I FOUND...

41:32.000 --> 41:34.500
WAS YOU.

41:42.375 --> 41:43.834
MITCH!
WHAT?

41:43.834 --> 41:45.166
MITCH.

41:45.166 --> 41:46.667
COME HERE.

41:46.667 --> 41:47.667
WHAT IS IT?

41:47.667 --> 41:48.667
JUST COME HERE.

41:48.667 --> 41:51.250
UM, HERE, SIT DOWN.

41:53.166 --> 41:55.458
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

41:55.458 --> 41:56.959
JUST THIS.

41:59.458 --> 42:02.000
LAST NIGHT,
YOU ASKED ME

42:02.000 --> 42:04.208
TO DEFINE THIS
RELATIONSHIP,

42:04.208 --> 42:05.875
AND I WASN'T
READY TO DO IT.

42:05.875 --> 42:07.750
I HAVE JUST BEEN
SO AFRAID OF--

42:07.750 --> 42:08.708
OF SCREWING UP,

42:08.708 --> 42:11.750
OF MAKING
THE SAME
MISTAKES TWICE.

42:13.250 --> 42:15.333
BUT I'M NOT
GONNA LET
THAT FEAR STOP US

42:15.333 --> 42:16.834
FROM BEING TOGETHER
ANYMORE.

42:19.000 --> 42:23.208
SO, IF OUR FATE
IS TO MAKE

42:23.208 --> 42:24.834
THE SAME MISTAKES
ALL OVER AGAIN,

42:24.834 --> 42:28.375
THEN BY GOD,
I HOPE WE MAKE
THOSE MISTAKES

42:28.375 --> 42:31.291
AS WELL AS WE DID
THE FIRST TIME.

42:33.917 --> 42:36.208
IS THAT A YES?

42:36.208 --> 42:38.917
WELL, YOU DIDN'T
ASK ME A QUESTION.

42:38.917 --> 42:41.125
YOU KNOW
THE QUESTION.

42:42.917 --> 42:43.792
YOU KNOW
THE ANSWER.
